name: Bulbasaur
summary: From birth, a sticky paste that it produces forms peculiar patterns on its body. Every Bulbasaur has a slightly different formation.

name: Ivysaur
summary: It burrows itself in sand, then waits for a prey to get closer, which is then showered by a substance similar to glue, blocking its escape.

name: Venusaur
summary: The clay-like substance it secretes is used as a super glue to patch up its den. It carries other Bulbasaur and Ivysaur in its vase.

name: Charmander
summary: The shiny gem on its chest is the very lifeforce of the Pokemon. In the past, poaching severely reduced this Pokemon's population.

name: Charmeleon
summary: Very impatient for its evolution, it feeds on the purest gems in the caves it lives in. While docile, it is quick to anger.

name: Charizard
summary: Usually docile, it becomes incredibly aggressive during mating season. The hand-like appendages on its back allow it to excavate dens inside sturdy gems.

name: Squirtle
summary: While underdeveloped, its tail has enough power to smash aside large boulders.

name: Wartortle
summary: It takes great care of its golden horns, symbol of its pride. If one dares to chip it, it'll throw its foe with a harsh swing of its tail.

name: Blastoise
summary: It uses its tail as a swinging mace, blowing away anything that comes close to it. Most do not survive this encounter unscathed.

name: Caterpie
summary: For protection, it releases a horrible stench from the antenna on its head to drive away enemies.

name: Metapod
summary: It is waiting for the moment to evolve. At this stage, it can only harden, so it remains motionless to avoid attack.

name: Butterfree
summary: It uses its wings to stun it's prey for an easy catch.

name: Weedle
summary: Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.

name: Kakuna
summary: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.

name: Beedrill
summary: May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.

name: Pidgey
summary: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.

name: Pidgeotto
summary: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this PokÃ©mon will fiercely peck at any intruder.

name: Pidgeot
summary: Revered as the "Wings of the Forest", they protect their territories fiercely and will rain down a maelstrom of petals upon offenders who trespass upon their canopies.

name: Rattata
summary: Although the rock formation on its tail makes it less nimble than its Kantonian brethren, it makes Ayreian Rattata a far more formidable opponent. They brutally swing their tails with in battle, oftentimes injuring themselves.

name: Raticate
summary: It's horn and teeth are extremely tough, able to take on even the harshest conditions without suffering even so much as a scratch. However, if either of the two were to ever shatter, this Pokemon will be shunned by its peers and treated as an outcast.

name: Spearow
summary: Populates more in grassy area than cold ones for unknown reasons. It leaves shards of ice wherever it sleeps.

name: Fearow
summary: A curious organ inside its abdomen allows it to mantain very cold temperatures no matter where it lives. When its life would be in peril, it incases itself in ice.

name: Ekans
summary: Moving silently and stealthily, it eats the eggs of birds, such as Pidgey and Spearow, whole.

name: Arbok
summary: To intimidate foes, it spreads its chest wide and makes eerie sounds by expelling air from its mouth.

name: Pikachu
summary: When Pikachu meet, they'll touch their tails together and exchange electricity through them as a form of greeting.

name: Raichu
summary: If its electric pouches run empty, it raises its tail to gather electricity from the atmosphere.

name: Sandshrew
summary: It burrows into the ground to create its nest. If hard stones impede its tunneling, it uses its sharp claws to shatter them and then carries on digging.

name: Sandslash
summary: It climbs trees by hooking on with its sharp claws. Sandslash shares the berries it gathers, dropping them down to Sandshrew waiting below the tree.

name: Nidoran♀
summary: It uses its hard incisor teeth to crush and eat berries. The tip of a female Nidoran's horn is a bit more rounded than the tip of a male's horn.

name: Nidorina
summary: If the group is threatened, these Pokémon will band together to assault enemies with a chorus of ultrasonic waves.

name: Nidoqueen
summary: It pacifies offspring by placing them in the gaps between the spines on its back. The spines will never secrete poison while young are present.

name: Nidoran♂
summary: The horn on a male Nidoran's forehead contains a powerful poison. This is a very cautious Pokémon, always straining its large ears.

name: Nidorino
summary: It's nervous and quick to act aggressively. The potency of its poison increases along with the level of adrenaline present in its body.

name: Nidoking
summary: One swing of its mighty tail can snap a telephone pole as if it were a matchstick.

name: Clefairy
summary: It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.

name: Clefable
summary: Their ears are sensitive enough to hear a pin drop from over a mile away, so they're usually found in quiet places.

name: Vulpix
summary: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.

name: Ninetales
summary: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1,000-year curse.

name: Jigglypuff
summary: Jigglypuff has top-notch lung capacity, even by comparison to other Pokémon. It won't stop singing its lullabies until its foes fall asleep.

name: Wigglytuff
summary: It's proud of its fur, which is fine and delicate. In particular, the curl on its forehead has a texture that's perfectly heavenly.

name: Zubat
summary: It emits ultrasonic waves from its mouth to check its surroundings. Even in tight caves, Zubat flies around with skill.

name: Golbat
summary: Its feet are tiny, but this Pokémon walks skillfully. It sneaks up on sleeping prey before sinking in its fangs and slurping up blood.

name: Oddish
summary: During the day, it stays in the cold underground to avoid the sun. It grows by bathing in moonlight.

name: Gloom
summary: Its pistils exude an incredibly foul odor. The horrid stench can cause fainting at a distance of 1.25 miles.

name: Vileplume
summary: It has the world's largest petals. With every step, the petals shake out heavy clouds of toxic pollen.

name: Paras
summary: Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.

name: Parasect
summary: The larger the mushroom on its back grows, the stronger the mushroom spores it scatters.

name: Venonat
summary: Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats bugs. It is attracted by light at night.

name: Venomoth
summary: The wings are covered with dustlike scales. Every time it flaps its wings, it looses highly toxic dust.

name: Diglett
summary: It sits in one location, only bothering those who try to pass directly through it.

name: Dugtrio
summary: It sits in one location, only bothering those who try to pass directly through it.

name: Meowth
summary: It washes its face regularly to keep the coin on its forehead spotless. It doesn't get along with Galarian Meowth.

name: Persian
summary: Its elegant and refined behavior clashes with that of the barbaric Perrserker. The relationship between the two is one of mutual disdain.

name: Psyduck
summary: As Psyduck gets stressed out, its headache gets progressively worse. It uses intense psychic energy to overwhelm those around it.

name: Golduck
summary: This Pokémon lives in gently flowing rivers. It paddles through the water with its long limbs, putting its graceful swimming skills on display.

name: Mankey
summary: It lives in treetop colonies. If one becomes enraged, the whole colony rampages for no reason.

name: Primeape
summary: It is always outrageously furious. If it gives chase, it will tenaciously track the target no matter how far.

name: Growlithe
summary: Extremely loyal, it will fearlessly bark at any opponent to protect its own Trainer from harm.

name: Arcanine
summary: The sight of it running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night has captivated many people.

name: Poliwag
summary: For Poliwag, swimming is easier than walking. The swirl pattern on its belly is actually part of the Pokémon's innards showing through the skin.

name: Poliwhirl
summary: Staring at the swirl on its belly causes drowsiness. This trait of Poliwhirl's has been used in place of lullabies to get children to go to sleep.

name: Poliwrath
summary: Its body is solid muscle. When swimming through cold seas, Poliwrath uses its impressive arms to smash through drift ice and plow forward.

name: Abra
summary: It seems this species of Abra became detached from psychic powers long ago. In spite of this, it still spends most of its time sleeping.

name: Kadabra

name: Alakazam
summary: A master of channeling latent energy throughout the region, it carves entire ecosystems energy signatures to its will to help its young learn to channel that power as well.

name: Machop
summary: Its whole body is composed of muscles. Even though it's the size of a human child, it can hurl 100 grown-ups.

name: Machamp

name: Bellsprout
summary: Its bud looks like a human face. Because of the bud, it is rumored to be a type of legendary mandrake plant.

name: Weepinbell
summary: It spits out Poison Powder to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of Acid.

name: Victreebel
summary: Once ingested into this Pokémon's body, even the hardest object will melt into nothing.

summary: It is impossible to distinguish from rocks. It slams against others in contests of hardness.

name: Graveler

name: Ponyta
summary: It can't run properly when it's newly born. As it races around with others of its kind, its legs grow stronger.

name: Rapidash
summary: This Pokémon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.

name: Slowpoke
summary: When this Pokémon's tail is soaked in water, sweetness seeps from it. Slowpoke uses this trait to lure in and fish up other Pokémon.

name: Slowbro
summary: Being bitten by a Shellder shocked this Pokémon into standing on two legs. If the Shellder lets go, it seems Slowbro will turn back into a Slowpoke.

name: Farfetch'd
summary: They use a plant stalk as a weapon, but not all of them use it in the same way. Several distinct styles of stalk fighting have been observed.

name: Doduo

name: Dofrio
summary: The head in the middle has a very nasty temper, while the head above it is whimsical and carefree.

name: Seel

name: Dewgong

name: Muk

summary: It swims facing backward by opening and closing its two-piece shell. It is surprisingly fast.

name: Gastly
summary: Its shell is extremely hard. It cannot be shattered, even with a bomb. The shell opens only when it is attacking.

name: Haunter
summary: Its tongue is made of gas. If licked, its victim starts shaking constantly until death eventually comes.

name: Gengar
summary: On the night of a full moon, if shadows move on their own and laugh, it must be Gengar's doing.

name: Onix
summary: It usually lives underground. It searches for food while boring its way through the ground at 50 miles per hour.

name: Drowzee
summary: If you think that you had a good dream but you can't remember it, a Drowzee has probably eaten it.

name: Hypno
summary: Seeing its swinging pendulum can induce sleep in three seconds, even in someone who just woke up.

name: Krabby

name: Kingler
summary: Its large and hard pincer has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, being so big, it is unwieldy to move.

name: Voltorb
summary: Usually found in shrines and caves, it stores heat inside its body to prepare for evolution.

name: Electrode
summary: It stores energy inside its ring, which it then releases violently as blasts of fire. It is considered a crop destroying god in some tribal villages.

name: Exeggcute
summary: These Pokémon get nervous when they're not in a group of six. The minute even one member of the group goes missing, Exeggcute become cowardly.

name: Exeggutor
summary: When they work together, Exeggutor's three heads can put out powerful psychic energy. Cloudy days make this Pokémon sluggish.

name: Cubone

name: Marowak

name: Koffing
summary: Far more cruel than its Kantonian counterpart, it is theorized that instead of absorbing toxic fumes to grow, it absorbs spirits.

name: Weezing
summary: It constantly exudes ephemeral gasses from its body. It is said that when someone inhales these gasses, they can see visions of the afterlife.

name: Rhyhorn
summary: Strong, but not too bright, this Pokémon can shatter even a skyscraper with its charging tackles.

name: Rhydon
summary: It begins walking on its hind legs after evolution. It can punch holes through boulders with its horn.

name: Chansey
summary: This species was once very slow. To protect their eggs from other creatures, these Pokémon became able to flee quickly.

name: Tangela
summary: Hidden beneath a tangle of vines that grows nonstop even if the vines are torn off, this Pokémon's true appearance remains a mystery.

name: Kangaskhan
summary: Although it's carrying its baby in a pouch on its belly, Kangaskhan is swift on its feet. It intimidates its opponents with quick jabs.

name: Horsea
summary: They swim with dance-like motions and cause whirlpools to form. Horsea compete to see which of them can generate the biggest whirlpool.

name: Seadra
summary: Seadra's mouth is slender, but its suction power is strong. In an instant, Seadra can suck in food that's larger than the opening of its mouth.

name: Goldeen
summary: Its dorsal, pectoral, and tail fins wave elegantly in water. That is why it is known as the Water Dancer.

name: Seaking
summary: Using its horn, it bores holes in riverbed boulders, making nests to prevent its eggs from washing away.

name: Staryu
summary: Fish Pokémon nibble at it, but Staryu isn't bothered. Its body regenerates quickly, even if part of it is completely torn off.

name: Starmie

name: Mr. Mime
summary: It's known for its top-notch pantomime skills. It protects itself from all sorts of attacks by emitting auras from its fingers to create walls.

name: Maimoraze
summary: This Pokemon gores anything in its path. When it charges, it emits a noise so loud, it can be heard from miles away.

name: Scyther

name: Jynx

name: Electabuzz
summary: Many power plants keep Ground-type Pokémon around as a defense against Electabuzz that come seeking electricity.

name: Magmar

name: Pinsir
summary: Its powerful carapace, harder than diamond, lets it shake off even tank shells. The leader of the pack has the most scars on its iron mantle.

name: Tauros
summary: When Tauros begins whipping itself with its tails, it's a warning that the Pokémon is about to charge with astounding speed.

name: Magikarp
summary: Its swimming muscles are weak, so it is easily washed away by currents. In places where water pools, you can see many Magikarp deposited there by the flow.

name: Gyarados

name: Lapras

name: Ditto
summary: It can reconstitute its entire cellular structure to change into what it sees, but it returns to normal when it relaxes.

name: Eevee
summary: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.

name: Vaporeon
summary: Its body's cellular structure is similar to the molecular composition of water. It can melt invisibly in water.

name: Jolteon
summary: If it is angered or startled, the fur all over its body bristles like sharp needles that pierce foes.

name: Flareon
summary: Once it has stored up enough heat, this Pokémon's body temperature can reach up to 1,700 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Porygon
summary: In recent years, this species has been very helpful in cyberspace. These Pokémon will go around checking to make sure no suspicious data exists.

name: Omanyte
summary: This Pokémon is a member of an ancient, extinct species. Omanyte paddles through water with its 10 tentacles, looking like it's just drifting along.

name: Omastar
summary: Weighed down by a large and heavy shell, Omastar couldn't move very fast. Some say it went extinct because it was unable to catch food.

name: Kabuto
summary: While some say this species has gone extinct, Kabuto sightings are apparently fairly common in some places.

name: Kabutops
summary: The cause behind the extinction of this species is unknown. Kabutops were aggressive Pokémon that inhabited warm seas.

name: Aerodactyl
summary: These Pokemon have existed for thousands of years, as they are as ancient as the forests they protect.

name: Snorlax
summary: For some reason, this Pokemon believes it is the king of the mountain, yet the only thing it does all day is sleep.

name: Articuno
summary: It's said that this Pokémon's beautiful blue wings are made of ice. Articuno flies over snowy mountains, its long tail fluttering along behind it.

name: Zapdos
summary: Zapdos is a legendary bird Pokémon. It's said that when Zapdos rubs its feathers together, lightning will fall immediately after.

name: Moltres
summary: It's one of the legendary bird Pokémon. When Moltres flaps its flaming wings, they glimmer with a dazzling red glow.

name: Dratini
summary: The first instance of Dratini sightings where under a meteor shower, so it is theorized that it came from space.

name: Dragonair
summary: Dragonair passively stores high amounts of energy in its armor, which is released all at once when its about to evolve.

name: Dragonite
summary: On par with legendary Pokemon, most humans spend their entire life not even knowing about their existence. The energy generated by them is otherwordly.

name: Mewtwo
summary: Created from the DNA of Mew, this Pokémon is a dangerous combination of overwhelming power and a savage heart.

name: Mew
summary: It's very intelligent and can use an incredible variety of moves. Many believe that all other Pokémon are descendants of this one.

name: Chikorita
summary: It uses the leaf on its head to determine the temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.

name: Bayleef
summary: The buds that ring its neck give off a spicy aroma that perks people up.

name: Meganium
summary: Meganium's breath has the power to revive dead grass and plants. It can make them healthy again.

name: Cyndaquil
summary: It is said that the ghostly flames spouting from its back burn brighter when specters are nearby.

name: Quilava
summary: Be careful if it turns its back during battle. It means that it will attack with the fire on its back.

name: Typhlosion
summary: It has a secret, devastating move. It rubs its blazing fur together to cause huge explosions.

name: Totodile
summary: Its powerful, well-developed jaws are capable of crushing anything. Even its Trainer must be careful.

name: Croconaw
summary: Once it bites down, it won't let go until it loses its fangs. New fangs quickly grow into place.

name: Feraligatr
summary: When it bites with its massive and powerful jaws, it shakes its head and savagely tears its victim up.

name: Sentret
summary: It stands on its tail so it can see a long way. If it spots an enemy, it cries loudly to warn its kind.

name: Furret
summary: It makes a nest to suit its long and skinny body. The nest is impossible for other Pokémon to enter.

name: Hoothoot
summary: It begins to hoot at the same time every day. Some Trainers use them in place of clocks.

name: Noctowl
summary: Its eyes are specially developed to enable it to see clearly even in murky darkness and minimal light.

name: Ledyba
summary: It is timid and clusters together with others. The fluid secreted by its feet indicates its location.

name: Ledian
summary: The spot patterns on its back grow larger or smaller depending on the number of stars in the night sky.

name: Spinarak
summary: It can blast a blinding light from its back to scare away predators.

name: Ariados
summary: It uses the bright light emanating from its torso to blind its prey before striking.

name: Crobat

name: Chinchou
summary: Its antennae, which evolved from a fin, have both positive and negative charges flowing through them.

name: Lanturn
summary: This Pokémon flashes a bright light that blinds its prey. This creates an opening for it to deliver an electrical attack.

name: Pichu
summary: Despite its small size, it can zap even adult humans. However, if it does so, it also surprises itself.

name: Cleffa
summary: According to local rumors, Cleffa are often seen in places where shooting stars have fallen.

name: Igglybuff
summary: Taking advantage of the softness of its body, Igglybuff moves as if bouncing. Its body turns a deep pink when its temperature rises.

name: Togepi
summary: This rare bird Pokemon hatches at the top of the coldest peaks, as its fire burns bright even at negative temperatures.

name: Togetic
summary: Its highly curious, but its incapability of flying holds it back from exploring new places. Its fire burns bright when its happy.

name: Natu
summary: Because its wings aren't yet fully grown, it has to hop to get around. It is always staring at something.

name: Xatu
summary: They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.

name: Mareep
summary: It stores lots of air in its soft fur, allowing it to stay cool in summer and warm in winter.

name: Flaaffy
summary: If its coat becomes fully charged with electricity, its tail lights up. It fires hair that zaps on impact.

name: Ampharos
summary: The tail's tip shines brightly and can be seen from far away. It acts as a beacon for lost people.

name: Bellossom
summary: Bellossom gather at times and appear to dance. They say that the dance is a ritual to summon the sun.

name: Marill
summary: Even after Marill swims in a cold sea, its water- repellent fur dries almost as soon as Marill leaves the water. That's why this Pokémon is never cold.

name: Azumarill
summary: These Pokémon create air-filled bubbles. When Azurill play in rivers, Azumarill will cover them with these bubbles.

name: Sudowoodo
summary: If a tree branch shakes when there is no wind, it's a Sudowoodo, not a tree. It hides from the rain.

name: Politoed
summary: At nightfall, these Pokémon appear on the shores of lakes. They announce their territorial claims by letting out cries that sound like shouting.

name: Hoppip
summary: The eye motifs on its wings have similar properties to hypnotizing devices. It feeds off of dreams.

name: Skiploom
summary: The "planteye" on top of its head releases a somniferous powder. Those who breathe it in fall into a deep coma.

name: Jumpluff
summary: By flashing bright lights from its limbs, it causes powerful headaches that eventually knock out its opponents. It flies lowly in the night, hunting for people's dreams.

name: Aipom
summary: Its tail is so powerful that it can use it to grab a tree branch and hold itself up in the air.

name: Sunkern
summary: It lives by drinking only dewdrops from under the leaves of plants. It is said that it eats nothing else.

name: Sunflora
summary: It gets energy from warm sunlight and is known for its habit of moving in pursuit of it.

name: Yanma
summary: If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.

name: Wooper
summary: When walking on land, it covers its body with a poisonous film that keeps its skin from dehydrating.

name: Quagsire
summary: Its body is always slimy. It often bangs its head on the river bottom as it swims but seems not to care.

name: Espeon
summary: It unleashes psychic power from the orb on its forehead. When its power is exhausted, the orb grows dull and dark.

name: Umbreon
summary: When this Pokémon becomes angry, its pores secrete a poisonous sweat, which it sprays at its opponent's eyes.

name: Murkrow
summary: Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.

name: Slowking

name: Misdreavus
summary: It likes playing mischievous tricks, such as screaming and wailing to startle people at night.

name: Unown
summary: Shaped like ancient writing, it is a huge mystery whether language or Unown came first.

name: Wobbuffet
summary: To keep its pitch-black tail hidden, it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.

name: Girafarig
summary: Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent by biting.

name: Pineco
summary: It looks just like a pinecone. Its shell protects it from bird Pokémon that peck it by mistake.

name: Forretress
summary: It remains immovably rooted to its tree. It scatters pieces of its hard shell to drive its enemies away.

name: Dunsparce
summary: It digs into the ground with its tail and makes a mazelike nest. It can fly just a little.

name: Gligar
summary: It flies straight at its target's face, then clamps down on the startled victim to inject poison.

name: Steelix
summary: It is said that if an Onix lives for over 100 years, its composition changes to become diamond-like.

name: Snubbull
summary: Small Pokémon flee from its scary face. It is, however, considered by women to be cute.

name: Granbull
summary: It can make most any Pokémon run away simply by opening its mouth wide to reveal its big fangs.

name: Qwilfish
summary: When faced with a larger opponent, it swallows as much water as it can to match the opponent's size.

name: Scizor
summary: Bulky pincers account for one third of Scizor's body weight. A single swing of one of these pincers will crush a boulder completely.

name: Shuckle
summary: It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.

name: Heracross
summary: With its Herculean powers, it can easily throw around an object that is 100 times its own weight.

name: Sneasel
summary: It has a cunning yet savage disposition. It waits for parents to leave their nests, and then it sneaks in to steal their eggs.

name: Teddiursa
summary: Before food becomes scarce in wintertime, its habit is to hoard food in many hidden locations.

name: Ursaring
summary: Although it has a large body, it is quite skilled at climbing trees. It eats and sleeps in the treetops.

name: Slugma
summary: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn't keep moving, its body will cool and harden.

name: Magcargo
summary: Its body is as hot as lava and is always billowing. Flames will occasionally burst from its shell.

name: Swinub
summary: It rubs its snout on the ground to find and dig up food. It sometimes discovers hot springs.

name: Piloswine
summary: If it charges at an enemy, the hairs on its back stand up straight. It is very sensitive to sound.

name: Corsola

name: Remoraid
summary: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a Mantine's underside to scavenge for leftovers.

name: Octillery
summary: It has a tendency to want to be in holes. It prefers rock crags or pots and sprays ink from them before attacking.

name: Delibird
summary: It has a generous habit of sharing its food with people and Pokémon, so it's always scrounging around for more food.

name: Mantine
summary: Mantine lurk in the dunes, and can leap from their hiding spot in a fraction of a second to devour their prey.

name: Skarmory
summary: Wild populations travel in groups lead by a single Skarmonarch who are protected by the Skarmory. They will ward off any invaders without mercy.

name: Houndour
summary: To corner prey, they check each other's location using barks that only they can understand.

name: Houndoom
summary: The flames it breathes when angry contain toxins. If they cause a burn, it will hurt forever.

name: Kingdra
summary: With the arrival of a storm at sea, this Pokémon will show itself on the surface. When a Kingdra and a Dragonite meet, a fierce battle ensues.

name: Phanpy
summary: It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.

name: Donphan
summary: An internal organ transmutes the outside moisture into warm water, which acts as a substitute to its blood in extremely cold temperatures.

name: Porygon2
summary: After artificial intelligence was implemented in Porygon2, the Pokémon began using a strange language that only other Porygon2 understand.

name: Stantler
summary: Stantler's magnificent antlers were once traded at high prices as works of art. As a result, this Pokémon was hunted close to extinction.

name: Smeargle
summary: Once it becomes an adult, it has a tendency to let its comrades plant footprints on its back.

name: Tyrogue
summary: Even though it is small, it can't be ignored because it will slug any handy target without warning.

name: Hitmontop
summary: The energy of the Shiny Stone enlightened this Pokemon to never before seen levels of serenity. It is almost impossible to distract.

name: Smoochum
summary: It waltzes around kissing anyone that it comes into contact with, while leaving nasty injuries that look like leech bites.

name: Elekid
summary: It's not good at storing electricity yet. This Pokémon sneaks into people's homes, looking for electrical outlets to eat electricity from.

name: Magby
summary: This Pokémon makes its home near volcanoes. At the end of the day, Magby soaks in magma, resting and recovering from the day's fatigue.

name: Miltank
summary: Miltank produces highly nutritious milk, so it's been supporting the lives of people and other Pokémon since ancient times.

name: Blissey
summary: Blissey lays mysterious eggs that are filled with happiness. It's said that anyone who eats a Blissey egg will start acting kindly to all others.

name: Raikou
summary: It embodies the speed of lightning. Its roars send shock waves shuddering through the air and shake the ground as if lightning bolts had come crashing down.

name: Entei
summary: It embodies the passion of magma. Born in the eruption of a volcano, it can send up massive bursts of fire that consume everything that they touch.

name: Suicune
summary: Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gracefulness. This Pokémon has the power to purify dirty water.

name: Larvitar
summary: Born deep underground, it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.

name: Pupitar
summary: Even sealed in its shell, it can move freely. Hard and fast, it has outstanding destructive power.

name: Tyranitar
summary: The quakes caused when it walks make even great mountains crumble and change the surrounding terrain.

name: Lugia
summary: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.

name: Ho-Oh
summary: A legend says that its body glows in seven colors. A rainbow is said to form behind it when it flies.

name: Celebi
summary: This Pokémon traveled through time to come from the future. It bolsters grass and trees with its own strength, and it can heal wounds, too.

name: Treecko
summary: Quite skittish, its diet primarily consists of twigs and leaves. It mimetizes with the environment to escape danger.

name: Grovyle
summary: The sheer power gained from evolution changed this Pokemon's metabolism, as it now behaves like an ambush predator.

name: Sceptile
summary: It can adapt to any and all environments, sitting at the top of the food chain. Because of this, they are an invasive species in most areas of the world.

name: Torchic
summary: Their immense ghostly energy allows them to summon additional limbs for a short time, but their inexperience makes them quite clumsy.

name: Combusken
summary: They blend in seemlessly with the shadows, which enable an easy ambush. When ignored, they will sometimes attack their own trainer.

name: Blaziken
summary: Wild and unpredictable, their legs kick the life out of their opponents. The floating limbs disappear if they stray too far from the main body.

name: Mudkip
summary: These Mudkips can be found sleeping soundly under frozen lakes. Their tails connect to the ice above, allowing them to sense vibrations from threats above.

name: Marshtomp
summary: Their icy blankets support their sleeping bodies and provide a shelter for small fish Pokemon. Unfortunately if they wander to close to its snoring mouth they may become a midnight snack.

name: Swampert
summary: Its hibernation can preserve itself for years past the typical life span of a Pokemon its size.

name: Poochyena
summary: It has a very tenacious nature. Its acute sense of smell lets it chase a chosen prey without ever losing track.

name: Mightyena
summary: It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.

name: Zigzagoon
summary: It marks its territory by rubbing its bristly fur on trees. This variety of Zigzagoon is friendlier and calmer than the kind native to Galar.

name: Linoone
summary: It uses its explosive speed and razor-sharp claws to bring down prey. Running along winding paths is not its strong suit.

name: Wurmple
summary: It lives among the tall grass and in forests. It repels attacks by raising up the spikes on its rear.

name: Silcoon
summary: It drinks dew that collects on its silk and waits for evolution. Its hard cocoon repels attacks.

name: Beautifly
summary: It has an aggressive nature. It stabs prey with its long, narrow mouth to drain the prey's fluids.

name: Cascoon
summary: It never forgets any attack it endured while in the cocoon. After evolution, it seeks payback.

name: Dustox
summary: It violently flutters its wings to scatter toxic dust when attacked. It becomes active after sunset.

name: Lotad
summary: It searches about for clean water. If it does not drink water for too long, the leaf on its head wilts.

name: Lombre
summary: It lives at the water's edge where it is sunny. It sleeps on a bed of water grass by day and becomes active at night.

name: Ludicolo
summary: The rhythm of bright, festive music activates Ludicolo's cells, making it more powerful.

name: Seedot
summary: It attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. Strong winds can sometimes make it fall.

name: Nuzleaf
summary: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.

name: Shiftry
summary: A Pokémon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe's mind and take preemptive action.

name: Taillow
summary: It dislikes cold seasons. They migrate to other lands in search of warmth, flying over 180 miles a day.

name: Swellow
summary: It dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. It catches its prey with sharp claws.

name: Wingull
summary: It soars on updrafts without flapping its wings. It makes a nest on sheer cliffs at the sea's edge.

name: Pelipper
summary: Skimming the water's surface, it dips its large bill in the sea, scoops up food and water, and carries it.

name: Ralts
summary: Its black plumage is said to bring misfortune to others near it.

name: Kirlia
summary: It uses wind currents to dance about in the night sky, even while hunting.

name: Gardevoir
summary: It has a latent power to read minds. A folktale tells that, long ago, this Pokemon and its "mirrored image" served a malicious king.

name: Surskit
summary: It appears as if it is skating on water. It draws prey with a sweet scent from the tip of its head.

name: Masquerain
summary: It flaps its four wings to hover and fly freely in any direction--to and fro and sideways.

name: Shroomish
summary: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.

name: Breloom
summary: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.

name: Slakoth
summary: If it eats just three leaves in a day, it is satisfied. Other than that, it sleeps for 20 hours a day.

name: Vigoroth
summary: Its stress level rises if it cannot keep moving constantly. Too much stress makes it feel sick.

name: Slaking
summary: It is the world's most slothful Pokémon. However, it can exert horrifying power by releasing pent-up energy all at once.

name: Nincada
summary: It can sometimes live underground for more than 10 years. It absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees.

name: Ninjask
summary: Its cry leaves a lasting headache if heard for too long. It moves so quickly that it is almost invisible.

name: Shedinja

name: Loudred

name: Exploud

name: Makuhita

name: Hariyama
summary: It loves to match power with big-bodied Pokémon. It can knock a truck flying with its arm thrusts.

name: Azurill
summary: Although Azurill are normally docile, an angry one will swing around the big ball on its tail and try to smash its opponents.

name: Nosepass
summary: Its magnetic nose consistently faces north. Travelers check Nosepass to get their bearings.

name: Skitty

name: Sableye
summary: This Pokémon is feared. When its gemstone eyes begin to glow with a sinister shine, it's believed that Sableye will steal people's spirits away.

name: Mawile
summary: It chomps with its gaping mouth. Its huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed.

name: Lairon

name: Meditite
summary: It eats just one berry a day. By enduring hunger, its spirit is tempered and made sharper.

name: Medicham
summary: Through yoga training, it gained the psychic power to predict its foe's next move.

summary: It stores electricity in its fur. It gives off sparks from all over its body in seasons when the air is dry.

name: Minun

name: Roselia
summary: If threatened, it will barrage its opponent with heavy blows from its rock-solid arms, which are also full of toxins.

name: Gulpin

name: Swalot
summary: It gulps anything that fits in its mouth. Its special enzymes can dissolve anything.

name: Camellum

name: Torkoal

name: Spoink

name: Grumpig
summary: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does an odd dance to gain control over foes.

name: Spinda
summary: The chances of two Spinda having identical spot patterns is less than one in four billion.

name: Trapinch

name: Vibrava

name: Swablu

name: Seviper
summary: Constant polishing makes the edge of the blade on its tail extremely sharp. It's Zangoose's archrival.

name: Lunatone
summary: Different types of music can be heard coming from it, depending on the mood it's in.

name: Solrock
summary: Solar energy is the source of its power, so it is strong during the daytime. When it spins, its body shines.

name: Barboach
summary: Its slimy body is hard to grasp. In one region, it is said to have been born from hardened mud.

name: Whiscash
summary: It makes its nest at the bottom of swamps. It will eat anything. If it is alive, Whiscash will eat it.

name: Corphish
summary: No matter how dirty the water in the river, it will adapt and thrive. It has a strong will to survive.

name: Crawdaunt

name: Baltoy
summary: It was discovered in ancient ruins. While moving, it constantly spins. It stands on one foot even when asleep.

name: Claydol
summary: It appears to have been born from clay dolls made by ancient people. It uses telekinesis to float and move.

name: Lileep

name: Armaldo
summary: After evolution, this Pokémon emerged onto land. Its lower body has become stronger, and blows from its tail are devastating.

name: Feebas
summary: Although unattractive and unpopular, this Pokémon's marvelous vitality has made it a subject of research.

name: Milotic
summary: Milotic has provided inspiration to many artists. It has even been referred to as the most beautiful Pokémon of all.

name: Castform
summary: It has the ability to change its form into the sun, the rain, or a snow cloud, depending on the weather.

name: Kecleon
summary: It changes its shading to match its surroundings so it can sneak up on prey. Only its belly patterns stay fixed.

name: Shuppet
summary: It loves vengeful emotions and hangs in rows under the eaves of houses where vengeful people live.

name: Banette
summary: Strong feelings of hatred turned a puppet into a Pokémon. If it opens its mouth, its cursed energy escapes.

name: Duskull
summary: If it finds bad children who won't listen to their parents, it will spirit them away ... or so it's said.

name: Dusclops
summary: It seeks drifting will-o'-the-wisps and sucks them into its empty body. What happens inside is a mystery.

name: Tropius
summary: A solitary Pokemon that resides in the depths of the jungle. It utilises powerful wingbeats to both fly and spread seeds, assisting the growth of its home.

name: Chimecho
summary: Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.

name: Absol
summary: Records released to the public just after the war state that Absol instinctively punished those that would bring harm to the forests near the conflict.

name: Wynaut
summary: It tends to move in a pack. Individuals squash against one another to toughen their spirits.

name: Snorunt
summary: It attaches itself to the ceiling of volcanic caves to absorb heat, which it then releases to fly around.

name: Glalie
summary: It can shoot concentrated energy waves from its horns. Its fire burns with a bright blue when it's enraged.

name: Spheal

name: Sealeo
summary: This Pokémon has a habit of spinning round things on its nose, whether those things are Poké Balls or Spheal.

name: Walrein

name: Clamperl
summary: It is protected by a sturdy shell. Once in a lifetime, it makes a magnificent pearl.

name: Huntail
summary: It lives deep in the sea. With a tail shaped like a small fish, it attracts unsuspecting prey.

name: Gorebyss
summary: Its swimming form is exquisitely elegant. With its thin mouth, it feeds on seaweed that grows between rocks.

name: Relicanth
summary: Said to be an incredibly old species gone extinct, a few specimen have begun appearing near the shores of Ayrei. They look lifeless at a glance.

name: Luvdisc
summary: It floats about pretending to be dead, waiting for its prey to approach before attacking.

name: Bagon
summary: Bagon is a solitary Pokémon that doesn't form groups with others of its kind. It also has a head hard enough to cleave a boulder in one strike.

name: Shelgon
summary: Shelgon ignores its hunger entirely, never eating any food. Apparently, Shelgon will evolve once all its energy stores are used up.

name: Salamence
summary: While basking in the joy of flight generally keeps it in high spirits, it turns into an uncontrollable menace if something angers it.

name: Beldum
summary: From its rear, Beldum emits a magnetic force that rapidly pulls opponents in. They get skewered on Beldum's sharp claws.

name: Metang
summary: Using magnetic forces to stay aloft, this Pokémon flies at high speeds, weaving through harsh mountain terrain in pursuit of prey.

name: Metagross
summary: Metagross is the result of the fusion of two Metang. This Pokémon defeats its opponents through use of its supercomputer-level brain.

name: Regirock
summary: Cutting-edge technology was used to study the internals of this Pokémon's rock body. However, nothing was found, not even brain or a heart.

name: Regice
summary: With cold air that can reach temperatures as low as -328 degrees Fahrenheit, Regice instantly freezes any creature that approaches it.

name: Registeel
summary: It's rumored that this Pokémon was born deep underground in the planet's mantle and that it emerged onto the surface 10,000 years ago.

name: Latias

name: Latios
summary: Latios has the ability to make others see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This Pokémon is intelligent and understands human speech.

name: Kyogre

name: Groudon
summary: Groudon is said to be the personification of the land itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Kyogre, as each sought to gain the power of nature.

name: Rayquaza
summary: Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years. Legends remain of how it put to rest the clash between Kyogre and Groudon.

name: Jirachi
summary: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.

name: Deoxys
summary: DNA from a space virus mutated and became a Pokémon. It appears where auroras are seen.

name: Turtwig
summary: It undertakes photosynthesis with its body, making oxygen. The leaf on its head wilts if it is thirsty.

name: Grotle
summary: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.

name: Torterra
summary: Small Pokémon occasionally gather on its unmoving back to begin building their nests.

name: Chimchar
summary: A Pokemon with a highly rowdy and unruly disposition, it frequently harasses travelers that enter its territory. However this behavior is not done out of malice, and instead out of curiosity.

name: Monferno
summary: It uses the poison on its tail both in combat and to mark its territory. It frequently gets into territorial disputes with Grafaiai.

name: Infernape
summary: The noxious fumes this pokemon is constantly emitting slows down and disorients its opponents. This in combination with Infernape's blinding speed make it a force to be reckoned with. name: Piplup
summary: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

name: Prinplup
summary: It lives a solitary life. Its wings deliver wicked blows that can snap even the thickest of trees.

name: Empoleon
summary: The three horns that extend from its beak attest to its power. The leader has the biggest horns.

name: Starly
summary: They flock in great numbers. Though small, they flap their wings with great power.

name: Staravia
summary: It flies around forests and fields in search of bug Pokémon. It stays within a huge flock.

name: Staraptor
summary: It has a savage nature. It will courageously challenge foes that are much larger.

name: Bidoof
summary: It constantly gnaws on logs and rocks to whittle down its front teeth. It nests alongside water.

name: Bibarel
summary: It makes its nest by damming streams with bark and mud. It is known as an industrious worker.

name: Kricketot
summary: When its antennae hit each other, it sounds like the music of a xylophone.

name: Kricketune
summary: It signals its emotions with its melodies. Scientists are studying these melodic patterns.

name: Shinx
summary: This Pokémon generates electricity by contracting its muscles. Excited trembling is a sign that Shinx is generating a tremendous amount of electricity.

name: Luxio
summary: Upon encountering an opponent, this Pokémon prepares for battle by extending its claws, which can put out 1,000,000 volts of electricity.

name: Luxray
summary: Seeing through solid objects uses up a lot of Luxray's electricity, so the Pokémon sleeps for long periods of time to store up energy.

name: Budew

name: Roserade

name: Cranidos
summary: A lifelong jungle dweller from 100 million years ago, it would snap obstructing trees with headbutts.

name: Rampardos
summary: Its skull is as hard as iron. It is a brute that tears down jungle trees while catching prey.

name: Shieldon
summary: It was generated from a fossil dug out of a layer of clay that was older than anyone knows. It has a sturdy face.

name: Bastiodon
summary: Any frontal attack is repulsed. It is a docile Pokémon that feeds on grass and berries.

name: Burmy
summary: If its cloak is broken in battle, it quickly remakes the cloak with materials nearby.

name: Wormadam
summary: When Burmy evolved, its cloak became a part of this Pokémon's body. The cloak is never shed.

name: Mothim
summary: It flutters around at night and steals honey from the Combee hive.

name: Combee
summary: The members of the trio spend all their time together. Each one has a slightly different taste in nectar.

name: Vespiquen
summary: It skillfully commands its grubs in battles with its enemies. The grubs are willing to risk their lives to defend Vespiquen.

name: Pachirisu
summary: The two sides of Pachirisu are a perfect parallel to each other. While the pale side is sluggish and lethargic, the other is hyperactive and dangerous.

name: Buizel
summary: It inflates the flotation sac around its neck and pokes its head out of the water to see what is going on.

name: Floatzel
summary: Its flotation sac developed as a result of pursuing aquatic prey. It can double as a rubber raft.

name: Cherubi
summary: It nimbly dashes about to avoid getting pecked by bird Pokémon that would love to make off with its small, nutrient-rich storage ball.

name: Cherrim
summary: The faint scent that emanates from its full blossom entices bug Pokémon to it.

name: Shellos
summary: This Pokémon's habitat shapes its physique. According to some theories, life in warm ocean waters causes this variation to develop.

name: Gastrodon
summary: It secretes a purple fluid to deter enemies. This fluid isn't poisonous. Instead, it's super sticky, and once it sticks, it's very hard to unstick.

name: Ambipom
summary: To eat, it deftly shucks nuts with its two tails. It rarely uses its arms now.

name: Drifloon
summary: They are very fond of people and the positivity they can express. They are often found parading large festivals and parties.

name: Drifblim
summary: This Pokemon always radiates with bright colors. Lost travelers or adventurers who follow it always find their way home.

name: Buneary

name: Lopunny

name: Mismagius

name: Honchkrow

name: Stunky

name: Happiny

name: Chatot
