summary: All Spiritomb's mischief and misdeeds compelled a traveler to use a mysterious spell to bind Spiritomb to an odd keystone.

name: Gible
summary: Gible attacks anything that moves, and it drags whatever it catches into the crevice that is its lair. Despite the big mouth, Gible's stomach is small.

name: Gabite
summary: Jewels are buried in the caves these Pokémon nest in, but you'll be torn apart by claws and fangs the moment you enter one of these caves.

name: Garchomp
summary: Garchomp makes its home in volcanic mountains. It flies through the sky as fast as a jet airplane, hunting down as much prey as it can.

name: Munchlax
summary: It feels immense joy from harassing others. You'll often find them in the wild, throwing rocks or snow at people and Pokemon.

name: Riolu
summary: Still new to the concept of Cyberspace, this Pokemon is the bioproduct of superfluous files from Lucario.

name: Lucario
summary: By controlling the virtual realm, it can mess with its opponent's data values. However, a virus may find its way inside Lucario when its guard is down.

name: Hippopotas
summary: It moves through the sands with its mouth open, swallowing sand along with its prey. It gets rid of the sand by spouting it from its nose.

name: Hippowdon
summary: Stones can get stuck in the ports on their bodies. Dwebble help dislodge such stones, so Hippowdon look after these Pokémon.

name: Skorupi
summary: After burrowing into the sand, it waits patiently for prey to come near. This Pokémon and Sizzlipede share common descent.

name: Drapion
summary: Its poison is potent, but it rarely sees use. This Pokémon prefers to use physical force instead, going on rampages with its car-crushing strength.

name: Croagunk
summary: Once diluted, its poison becomes medicinal. This Pokémon came into popularity after a pharmaceutical company chose it as a mascot.

name: Toxicroak
summary: It bounces toward opponents and gouges them with poisonous claws. No more than a scratch is needed to knock out its adversaries.

name: Carnivine
summary: It binds itself to trees in marshes. It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling drool and gulps them down.

name: Finneon
summary: After long exposure to sunlight, the patterns on its tail fins shine vividly when darkness arrives.

name: Lumineon
summary: To avoid detection by predators, it crawls along the seafloor using the two fins on its chest.

name: Mantyke
summary: It burrows underground and shocks it's enemy from below as a surprise attack.

name: Snover
summary: It lives on snowy mountains. It sinks its legs into the snow to absorb water and keep its own temperature down.

name: Abomasnow
summary: If it sees any packs of Darumaka going after Snover, it chases them off, swinging its sizable arms like hammers.

name: Weavile
summary: They attack their quarry in packs. Prey as large as Mamoswine easily fall to the teamwork of a group of Weavile.

name: Magnezone
summary: Some say that Magnezone receives signals from space via the antenna on its head and that it's being controlled by some mysterious being.

name: Lickilicky
summary: Lickilicky can do just about anything with its tongue, which is as dexterous as the human hand. In contrast, Lickilicky's use of its fingers is clumsy.

name: Rhyperior
summary: It can load up to three projectiles per arm into the holes in its hands. What launches out of those holes could be either rocks or Roggenrola.

name: Tangrowth
summary: Vine growth is accelerated for Tangrowth living in warm climates. If the vines grow long, Tangrowth shortens them by tearing parts of them off.

name: Electivire
summary: In terms of electrical-energy output, Electivire is one of the best among all Electric Pokémon. It discharges high-voltage currents from its tails.

name: Magmortar
summary: When Magmortar inhales deeply, the fire burning in its belly intensifies, rising in temperature to over 3,600 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Togekiss
summary: These Pokémon are never seen anywhere near conflict or turmoil. In recent times, they've hardly been seen at all.

name: Yanmega
summary: This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.

name: Leafeon
summary: Galarians favor the distinctive aroma that drifts from this Pokémon's leaves. There's a popular perfume made using that scent.

name: Glaceon
summary: The coldness emanating from Glaceon causes powdery snow to form, making it quite a popular Pokémon at ski resorts.

name: Gliscor
summary: Its flight is soundless. It uses its lengthy tail to carry off its prey. Then its elongated fangs do the rest.

name: Mamoswine
summary: It looks strong, and that's exactly what it is. As the weather grows colder, its ice tusks grow longer, thicker, and more impressive.

name: Porygon-Z
summary: Porygon-Z had a program installed to allow it to move between dimensions, but the program also caused instability in Porygon-Z's behavior.

name: Gallade
summary: With its latent powers, it can force anyone to do its bidding. A folktale tells that, long ago, this Pokemon and its "mirrored image" served a malicious king.

name: Gyropass
summary: It rotates endlessly. This behavior has made it the subject of many theories.

name: Dusknoir
summary: With the mouth on its belly, Dusknoir swallows its target whole. The soul is the only thing eaten. Dusknoir disgorges the body before departing.

name: Froslass
summary: It can be seen regularly taking command of others. However, it prefers to work with its likeminded counterpart.

name: Rotom
summary: One boy's invention led to the development of many different machines that take advantage of Rotom's unique capabilities.

name: Uxie
summary: Known as "The Being of Knowledge." It is said that it can wipe out the memory of those who see its eyes.

name: Mesprit
summary: Known as "The Being of Emotion." It taught humans the nobility of sorrow, pain, and joy.

name: Azelf
summary: Known as "The Being of Willpower." It sleeps at the bottom of a lake to keep the world in balance.

name: Dialga
summary: A Pokémon spoken of in legend. It is said that time began moving when Dialga was born.

name: Palkia
summary: It is said to live in a gap in the spatial dimension parallel to ours. It appears in mythology.

name: Heatran
summary: It dwells in volcanic caves. It digs in with its cross-shaped feet to crawl on ceilings and walls.

name: Regigigas
summary: It is said to have made Pokémon that look like itself from a special ice mountain, rocks, and magma.

name: Giratina
summary: This Pokémon is said to live in a world on the reverse side of ours, where common knowledge is distorted and strange.

name: Cresselia
summary: Those who sleep holding Cresselia's feather are assured of joyful dreams. It is said to represent the crescent moon.

name: Phione
summary: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.

name: Manaphy
summary: It starts its life with a wondrous power that permits it to bond with any kind of Pokémon.

name: Darkrai
summary: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

name: Shaymin
summary: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.

name: Arceus
summary: It is told in mythology that this Pokémon was born before the universe even existed.

name: Victini
summary: This Pokémon brings victory. It is said that Trainers with Victini always win, regardless of the type of encounter.

name: Snivy
summary: When they're in good health, the liquid metal they cover themselves with doesn't stick to surfaces.

name: Servine
summary: The liquid metal its body is made of is so dense that its an incredibly heavy Pokemon, despite its minute size.

name: Serperior
summary: Its body is made up by more than 85% of liquid metal. To protect itself, it slowly exhales a noxious gas, even while sleeping.

name: Tepig
summary: It can be seen sleeping soundly in lava lakes. It is thought that Tepig are born whenever a volcano erupts.

name: Pignite
summary: The black smoke Pignite is constantly emitting serves both as a way to disorient its opponents and as protection for its body.

name: Emboar
summary: Ayreian Emboar use brute force to claim massive territories to rule over. Territorial disputes between two Emboar only end in scorched earth and ruin.

name: Oshawott
summary: This Pokémon endlessly picks fights with opponents tougher than itself. It has a strong sense of honor.

name: Dewott
summary: Since evolving, it's feather dual blades are now capable of cutting through solid steel with ease.

name: Samurott
summary: It can cut through clouds with one swing of its sword, the territory of this Pokémon is identifiable by looking up and seeing a scarred horizon.

name: Patrat
summary: Extremely cautious, one of them will always be on the lookout, but it won't notice a foe coming from behind.

name: Watchog
summary: When they see an enemy, their tails stand high, and they spit the seeds of berries stored in their cheek pouches.

name: Lillipup
summary: This Pokémon is courageous but also cautious. It uses the soft fur covering its face to collect information about its surroundings.

name: Herdier
summary: Herdier is a very smart and friendly Pokémon. So much so that there's a theory that Herdier was the first Pokémon to partner with people.

name: Stoutland
summary: Stoutland is immensely proud of its impressive moustache. It's said that moustache length is what determines social standing among this species.

name: Purrloin
summary: Opponents that get drawn in by its adorable behavior come away with stinging scratches from its claws and stinging pride from its laughter.

name: Liepard
summary: This stealthy Pokémon sneaks up behind prey without making any sound at all. It competes with Thievul for territory.

name: Pansage
summary: It's good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It's kind enough to share them with friends.

name: Simisage
summary: Ill tempered, it fights by swinging its barbed tail around wildly. The leaf growing on its head is very bitter.

name: Pansear
summary: This Pokémon lives in caves in volcanoes. The fire within the tuft on its head can reach 600 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Simisear
summary: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.

name: Panpour
summary: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. Plants that receive its water grow large.

name: Simipour
summary: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.

name: Munna
summary: It eats dreams and releases mist. The mist is pink when it's eating a good dream, and black when it's eating a nightmare.

name: Musharna
summary: It drowses and dreams all the time. It's best to leave it be if it's just woken up, as it's a terrible grump when freshly roused from sleep.

name: Pidove
summary: It snobs other Pokemon, even shoving them aside when there's food nearby. Due to its small size, most of the time it's sent running with its tail between its legs.

name: Tranquill
summary: Adored by old ladies, they are often found in videos online due to their grumpy nature. Seeing one in the wild is a rare sight.

name: Unfezant
summary: In the past, the commanding presence of Unfezant was enough to make entire civilizations bow to it. Those that stood in its way were showered by powerful toxins.

name: Unfezant
summary: Narcissistic like little else, they often annoy other Pokemon and end up in fights. Unlike Pidove's, the powerful legs of an Unfezant are a fierce and effective weapon.

name: Unfezant
summary: Narcissistic like little else, they often annoy other Pokemon and end up in fights. Unlike Pidove's, the powerful legs of an Unfezant are a fierce and effective weapon.

name: Blitzle
summary: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.

name: Zebstrika
summary: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

name: Roggenrola
summary: When it detects a noise, it starts to move. The energy core inside it makes this Pokémon slightly warm to the touch.

name: Boldore
summary: It relies on sound in order to monitor what's in its vicinity. When angered, it will attack without ever changing the direction it's facing.

name: Gigalith
summary: Although its energy blasts can blow away a dump truck. They have a limitation, they can only be fired when the sun is out.

name: Woobat
summary: While inside a cave, if you look up and see lots of heart-shaped marks lining the walls, it's evidence that Woobat live there.

name: Swoobat
summary: The auspicious shape of this Pokémon's nose apparently led some regions to consider Swoobat a symbol of good luck.

name: Drilbur
summary: It's a digger, using its claws to burrow through the ground. It causes damage to vegetable crops, so many farmers have little love for it.

name: Excadrill
summary: It's not uncommon for tunnels that appear to have formed naturally to actually be a result of Excadrill's rampant digging.

name: Audino
summary: Audino's sense of hearing is superb. Not even a pebble rolling along over a mile away will escape Audino's ears.

name: Timburr
summary: It loves helping out with construction projects. It loves it so much that if rain causes work to halt, it swings its log around and throws a tantrum.

name: Gurdurr
summary: Gurdurr excels at demolition. Construction is not its forte. In any case, there's skill in the way this Pokémon wields its metal beam.

name: Conkeldurr
summary: Concrete mixed by Conkeldurr is much more durable than normal concrete, even when the compositions of the two materials are the same.

name: Tympole
summary: It uses sound waves to communicate with others of its kind. People and other Pokémon species can't hear its cries of warning.

name: Palpitoad
summary: On occasion, their cries are sublimely pleasing to the ear. Palpitoad with larger lumps on their bodies can sing with a wider range of sounds.

name: Seismitoad
summary: The vibrating of the bumps all over its body causes earthquake-like tremors. Seismitoad and Croagunk are similar species.

name: Throh
summary: It performs throwing moves with first-rate skill. Over the course of many battles, Throh's belt grows darker as it absorbs its wearer's sweat.

name: Sawk
summary: If you see a Sawk training in the mountains in its single-minded pursuit of strength, it's best to quietly pass by.

name: Sewaddle
summary: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.

name: Swadloon
summary: It protects itself from the cold by wrapping up in leaves. It stays on the move, eating leaves in forests.

name: Leavanny
summary: It keeps its eggs warm with heat from fermenting leaves. It also uses leaves to make warm wrappings for Sewaddle.

name: Venipede
summary: Known to be territorial, they gnaw at mineral deposits and use them as fuel for their electricity.

name: Whirlipede
summary: Whirlipedes are often domesticated, as their excess amount of electricity through evolution allows them to power generators without strain.

name: Scolipede
summary: Seemingly coming from outside of the region, they host the capacity to power entire cities with the electricity circuiting through their body.

name: Cottonee
summary: They go wherever the wind takes them. On rainy days, their bodies are heavier, so they take shelter beneath big trees.

name: Whimsicott
summary: Riding whirlwinds, they appear. These Pokémon sneak through gaps into houses and cause all sorts of mischief.

name: Petilil
summary: Petilil appears around sources of clean water. Boiling leaves from this Pokémon's head results in a liquid that's sometimes used as a bug repellent.

name: Lilligant
summary: It's believed that even first-rate gardeners have a hard time getting the flower on a Lilligant's head to bloom

name: Basculin
summary: Anglers love the fight this Pokémon puts up on the hook. And there are always more to catch. Many people release them into lakes illicitly.

name: Sandile
summary: Sandile is small, but its legs and lower body are powerful. Pushing snow aside as it goes, Sandile moves through the tundra as if it's swimming.

name: Krokorok
summary: Although this Pokémon has specialized eyes that allow it to see well in water, Krokorok aren't adept swimmers.

name: Krookodile
summary: This Pokemon is known as the Bully of the Tundra. Krookodile's mighty jaws can bite through permafrost with ease.

name: Darumaka
summary: It derives its power from fire burning inside its body. If the fire dwindles, this Pokémon will immediately fall asleep.

name: Darmanitan
summary: This Pokémon's power level rises along with the temperature of its fire, which can reach 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Maractus
summary: With noises that could be mistaken for the rattles of maracas, it creates an upbeat rhythm, startling bird Pokémon and making them fly off in a hurry.

name: Dwebble
summary: The plant on top of its back secretes a sticky substance similar to glue. Sometimes, Dwebble will have items attached to it, like Heart Scales.

name: Crustle
summary: This highly territorial Pokémon prefers dry climates. It won't come out of its boulder on rainy days.

name: Scraggy
summary: If it locks eyes with you, watch out! Nothing and no one is safe from the reckless headbutts of this troublesome Pokémon.

name: Scrafty
summary: While mostly known for having the temperament of an aggressive ruffian, this Pokémon takes very good care of its family, friends, and territory.

name: Sigilyph
summary: Psychic power allows these Pokémon to fly. Some say they were the guardians of an ancient city. Others say they were the guardians' emissaries.

name: Yamask
summary: The spirit of a person from a bygone age became this Pokémon. It rambles through ruins, searching for someone who knows its face.

name: Cofagrigus
summary: There are many depictions of Cofagrigus decorating ancient tombs. They're symbols of the wealth that kings of bygone eras had.

name: Tirtouga
summary: This Pokémon inhabited ancient seas. Although it can only crawl, it still comes up onto land in search of prey.

name: Carracosta
summary: Carracosta completely devours its prey, bones, shells, and all. Because of this, Carracosta's own shell grows thick and sturdy.

name: Archen
summary: While its underdeveloped wings prevent it from flying, it can jump up to 30 feet in the air.

name: Archeops
summary: Scientists believe this was the true form of Archeops, millions of years ago. Its legs are powerful enough to overturn a truck, but it is only able to glide small distances.

name: Trubbish
summary: Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you leave trash lying around, you could even find one of these Pokémon living in your room.

name: Garbodor
summary: This Pokémon eats trash, which turns into poison inside its body. The main component of the poison depends on what sort of trash was eaten.

name: Zorua
summary: It attracts lost humans and Pokemon with mirages, which it then rescues from the unforgiving desert heat. Travelers dispersed in the dunes are usually found near an oasis.

name: Zoroark
summary: It attracts lost humans and Pokemon with mirages, which it then rescues from the unforgiving desert heat. Travelers dispersed in the dunes are usually found near an oasis.

name: Minccino
summary: Old ladies adore this Pokemon, even if it tends to steal jewelry while no one's looking. Everyone finds it adorable though.

name: Cinccino
summary: The patterns of Cinccino help it to mimethize in the wild, while it uses its electric powers to steal all sorts of metallic treasure.

name: Gothita
summary: Even when nobody seems to be around, Gothita can still be heard making a muted cry. Many believe it's speaking to something only it can see.

name: Gothorita
summary: On nights when the stars shine, this Pokémon's psychic power is at its strongest. It's unknown just what link Gothorita has to the greater universe.

name: Gothitelle
summary: It has tremendous psychic power, but it dislikes conflict. It's also able to predict the future based on the movement of the stars.

name: Solosis
summary: Its body is encapsulated in liquid, but if it takes a heavy blow, the liquid will leak out.

name: Duosion
summary: Its body is encapsulated in liquid, but if it takes a heavy blow, the liquid will leak out.

name: Reuniclus
summary: Reuniclus might be one of the first complex lifeforms that appeared on the planet, as the water coating it produces easily survives even the strongest pressure underwater.

name: Ducklett
summary: This Pokemon can only make friends with others they deem as less beautiful then them. It has a deep hatred for Pokemon more beautiful than itself.

name: Swanna
summary: It hunts down butterfly-like Pokemon and takes their wings to add to its own. It's rumored this Pokemon caused the mass reduction in Ayrei's Vivillon population.

name: Vanillite
summary: Unable to survive in cold areas, it makes itself comfortable by breathing out air to cause sandstorms. It burrows into the sand to sleep.

name: Vanillish
summary: It blasts enemies with hot air reaching 200 degrees Fahrenheit, burning them. But it spares their lives afterwards. It's a kind PokÃ©mon.

name: Vanilluxe
summary: Its outer shell is as hot as the inside of an active volcano. It obliviously burns everything in its vicinity to a crisp, be it friend or foe.

name: Deerling
summary: At night, their horns glow with light, allowing them to communicate with other members of the herd. They are believed to have near-human intelligence.

name: Sawsbuck
summary: These Sawsbuck grow more powerful the more knowledge they acquire, signified by the glow of their antlers. The ones with the most luminous antlers are the leaders of the herd.

name: Emolga
summary: This Pokémon absolutely loves sweet berries. Sometimes it stuffs its cheeks full of so much food that it can't fly properly.

name: Karrablast
summary: For some reason they evolve when they receive electrical energy while they are attacking Shelmet.

name: Escavalier
summary: It charges its enemies, lances at the ready. An image of one of its duels is captured in a famous painting of Escavalier clashing with Sirfetch'd.

name: Foongus
summary: The spores released from this Pokémon's hands are highly poisonous, but when thoroughly dried, the spores can be used as stomach medicine.

name: Amoonguss
summary: This Pokémon puffs poisonous spores at its foes. If the spores aren't washed off quickly, they'll grow into mushrooms wherever they land.

name: Frillish
summary: It envelops its prey in its veillike arms and draws it down to the deeps, five miles below the ocean's surface.

name: Jellicent
summary: Whenever a full moon hangs in the night sky, schools of Jellicent gather near the surface of the sea, waiting for their prey to appear.

name: Alomomola
summary: It gently holds injured and weak Pokémon in its fins. Its special membrane heals their wounds.

name: Joltik
summary: Joltik can be found clinging to other Pokémon. It's soaking up static electricity because it can't produce a charge on its own.

name: Galvantula
summary: It launches electrified fur from its abdomen as its means of attack. Opponents hit by the fur could be in for three full days and nights of paralysis.

name: Ferroseed
summary: Mossy caves are their preferred dwellings. Enzymes contained in mosses help Ferroseed's spikes grow big and strong.

name: Ferrothorn
summary: This Pokémon scrapes its spikes across rocks, and then uses the tips of its feelers to absorb the nutrients it finds within the stone.

name: Klink
summary: The two minigears that compose this Pokémon are closer than twins. They mesh well only with each other.

name: Klang
summary: When Klang goes all out, the minigear links up perfectly with the outer part of the big gear, and this Pokémon's rotation speed increases sharply.

name: Klinklang
summary: From its spikes, it launches powerful blasts of electricity. Its red core contains an enormous amount of energy.

name: Tynamo
summary: One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.

name: Eelektrik
summary: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.

name: Eelektross
summary: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

name: Elgyem
summary: If this Pokémon stands near a TV, strange scenery will appear on the screen. That scenery is said to be from its home.

name: Beheeyem
summary: Sometimes found drifting above wheat fields, this Pokémon can control the memories of its opponents.

name: Litwick
summary: The flame on its head keeps its body slightly warm. This Pokémon takes lost children by the hand to guide them to the spirit world.

name: Lampent
summary: It lurks in cities, pretending to be a lamp. Once it finds someone whose death is near, it will trail quietly after them.

name: Chandelure
summary: This Pokémon haunts dilapidated mansions. It sways its arms to hypnotize opponents with the ominous dancing of its flames.

name: Axew
summary: They subsist on ruby gemstones found deep within the region, it's theorized that these Pokemon have been adapted to this diet over the course of many years.

name: Fraxure
summary: They are very protective of their peers, and in equal measures are they territorial. Their ruby tusks can channel energy through stones to amplify their strength.

name: Haxorus
summary: They have become very rare due to poachers seeking their tusks. As such, the remaining Haxorus are ruthless, and known to collapse entire mountains to protect their kin.

name: Cubchoo
summary: When this Pokémon is in good health, its snot becomes thicker and stickier. It will smear its snot on anyone it doesn't like.

name: Beartic
summary: It swims energetically through frigid seas. When it gets tired, it freezes the seawater with its breath so it can rest on the ice.

name: Cryogonal
summary: When the weather gets hot, these Pokémon turn into water vapor. Cryogonal are almost never seen during summer.

name: Shelmet
summary: When attacked, it tightly shuts the lid of its shell. This reaction fails to protect it from Karrablast, however, because they can still get into the shell.

name: Accelgor
summary: It moves with blinding speed and lobs poison at foes. Featuring Accelgor as a main character is a surefire way to make a movie or comic popular.

name: Stunfisk
summary: For some reason, this Pokémon smiles slightly when it emits a strong electric current from the yellow markings on its body.

name: Mienfoo
summary: Though small, Mienfoo's temperament is fierce. Any creature that approaches Mienfoo carelessly will be greeted with a flurry of graceful attacks.

name: Mienshao
summary: When Mienshao comes across a truly challenging opponent, it will lighten itself by biting off the fur on its arms.

name: Druddigon
summary: Devious and opportunistic, it flies through Cyberspace in search of vulnerable files to infect. Unreliable sources say that they were made by a group of hackers that opposed the war.

name: Golett
summary: This Pokémon was created from clay. It received orders from its master many thousands of years ago, and it still follows those orders to this day.

name: Golurk
summary: There's a theory that inside Golurk is a perpetual motion machine that produces limitless energy, but this belief hasn't been proven.

name: Pawniard
summary: It uses river stones to maintain the cutting edges of the blades covering its body. These sharpened blades allow it to bring down opponents.

name: Bisharp
summary: It's accompanied by a large retinue of Pawniard. Bisharp keeps a keen eye on its minions, ensuring none of them even think of double-crossing it.

name: Bouffalant
summary: These Pokémon live in herds of about 20 individuals. Bouffalant that betray the herd will lose the hair on their heads for some reason.

name: Rufflet
summary: If it spies a strong Pokémon, Rufflet can't resist challenging it to a battle. But if Rufflet loses, it starts bawling.

name: Braviary
summary: Because this Pokémon is hotheaded and belligerent, it's Corviknight that's taken the role of transportation in Galar.

name: Vullaby
summary: Vullaby grow quickly. Bones that have gotten too small for older Vullaby to wear often get passed down to younger ones in the nest.

name: Mandibuzz
summary: They adorn themselves with bones. There seem to be fashion trends among them, as different bones come into and fall out of popularity.

name: Heatmor
summary: There's a hole in its tail that allows it to draw in the air it needs to keep its fire burning. If the hole gets blocked, this Pokémon will fall ill.

name: Durant
summary: With their large mandibles, these Pokémon can crunch their way through rock. They work together to protect their eggs from Sandaconda.

name: Deino
summary: When it encounters something, its first urge is usually to bite it. If it likes what it tastes, it will commit the associated scent to memory.

name: Zweilous
summary: Their two heads will fight each other over a single piece of food. Zweilous are covered in scars even without battling others.

name: Hydreigon
summary: It brings famine wherever it goes, as its insatiable hunger cannot be contained. Hydreigon usage is heavily regulated, as most trainers cannot quell them.

name: Larvesta
summary: Larvesta's body is warm all over. It spouts fire from the tips of its horns to intimidate predators and scare prey.

name: Volcarona
summary: Volcarona scatters burning scales. Some say it does this to start fires. Others say it's trying to rescue those that suffer in the cold.

name: Cobalion
summary: It has a body and heart of steel. It worked with its allies to punish people when they hurt Pokémon.

name: Terrakion
summary: Spoken of in legend, this Pokémon used its phenomenal power to destroy a castle in its effort to protect Pokémon.

name: Virizion
summary: Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponents with its swift movements.

name: Tornadus
summary: Tornadus expels massive energy from its tail, causing severe storms. Its power is great enough to blow houses away.

name: Thundurus
summary: The spikes on its tail discharge immense bolts of lightning. It flies around the Unova region firing off lightning bolts.

name: Reshiram
summary: When Reshiram's tail flares, the heat energy moves the atmosphere and changes the world's weather.

name: Zekrom
summary: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

name: Landorus
summary: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as "The Guardian of the Fields."

name: Kyurem
summary: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

name: Keldeo
summary: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.

name: Meloetta
summary: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

name: Genesect
summary: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.

name: Chespin
summary: Such a thick shell of wood covers its head and back that even a direct hit from a truck wouldn't faze it.

name: Quilladin
summary: They strengthen their lower bodies by running into one another. They are very kind and won't start fights.

name: Chesnaught
summary: When it takes a defensive posture with its fists guarding its face, it could withstand a bomb blast.

name: Fennekin
summary: This Pokemon is only seen near secluded icy lakes. They only emerge to drink from the springs when they are alone.

name: Braixen
summary: The budding voices of these foxes produce may produce beautiful auroras during the night. However, they are quick to stop and run away should they be discovered.

name: Delphox
summary: "Travelers may be able to witness the songs of these foxes during an aurora. However, their voices also enhance the ice they use to chase off unwanted company."

name: Froakie
summary: Is is able to stay completely still for hours at a time, but when one draws near it, it will suddenly awaken and escape to below the water's surface.

name: Frogadier
summary: Sightings of this Pokemon have only been reported relatively recently. It was once thought that wild Froakie directly evolved to Greninja, and that trainer intervention delayed this evolution.

name: Greninja
summary: Completely in tune with nature, it is a symbol of peace and prosperity. A Greninja is the hallmark of a healthy and flourishing fresh water ecosystem.

name: Bunnelby
summary: It's very sensitive to danger. The sound of Corviknight's flapping will have Bunnelby digging a hole to hide underground in moments.

name: Diggersby
summary: The fur on its belly retains heat exceptionally well. People used to make heavy winter clothing from fur shed by this Pokémon.

name: Fletchling
summary: "The small ember that rests atop their head doesn't burn out even when doused in water. They will often stick their heads into the burrows of their prey to lure them out with the flames."

name: Fletchinder
summary: "Now able to fly for days at a time, Ayreian Fletchinders hunt diligently by the sea, picking off even the most agile swimmers thanks to its feathers not being hindered by water."

name: Fleumflame
summary: "Historically regarded as heralds or signs of rainfall to come in the wake of a drought, Fleumflames are often seen soaring across the ocean, where they can dive hundreds of meters beneath the surface to hunt prey that are drawn to their flame's light."

name: Scatterbug
summary: The powder that covers its body regulates its temperature, so it can live in any region or climate.

name: Spewpa
summary: The beaks of bird Pokémon can't begin to scratch its stalwart body. To defend itself, it spews powder.

name: Vivillon
summary: The patterns on this Pokémon's wings depend on the climate and topography of its habitat. It scatters colorful scales.

name: Litleo
summary: It can be found in greatly polluted areas. The fumes that emit from their mane can knock out a full-grown adult.

name: Pyroar
summary: Adapted to the polluted grounds that have become its territory, it preys upon the smaller Pokémon in the urban landscape and defends its territory viciously from humankind.

name: Flabébé
summary: When it finds a flower it likes, it dwells on that flower its whole life long. It floats in the wind's embrace with an untroubled heart.

name: Floette
summary: When the flowers of a well-tended flower bed bloom, it appears and celebrates with an elegant dance.

name: Florges
summary: In times long past, governors of castles would invite Florges to create flower gardens to embellish the castle domains.

name: Skiddo
summary: Amicable and excitable beings, Skiddo will often frolic along the shorelines with people and Pokemon alike.

name: Gogoat
summary: Living on the oceans surface, they race along the waves and are revered by sailors for their ability to calm the sea itself.

name: Pancham
summary: Wanting to make sure it's taken seriously, Pancham's always giving others a glare. But if it's not focusing, it ends up smiling.

name: Pangoro
summary: Angrier than a raging inferno, it pummels opponents with a fiery might. The fire emanating from its body is hot enough to melt the metal of a jet plane.

name: Furfrou
summary: Historically, in the Kalos region, these Pokémon were the designated guardians of the king.

name: Espurr
summary: There's enough psychic power in Espurr to send a wrestler flying, but because this power can't be controlled, Espurr finds it troublesome.

name: Meowstic
summary: Revealing the eyelike patterns on the insides of its ears will unleash its psychic powers. It normally keeps the patterns hidden, however.

name: Honedge
summary: Honedge's soul once belonged to a person who was killed a long time ago by the sword that makes up Honedge's body.

name: Doublade
summary: The two swords employ a strategy of rapidly alternating between offense and defense to bring down their prey.

name: Aegislash
summary: Its potent spectral powers allow it to manipulate others. It once used its powers to force people and Pokémon to build a kingdom to its liking.

name: Spritzee
summary: A scent pouch within this Pokémon's body allows it to create various scents. A change in its diet will alter the fragrance it produces.

name: Aromatisse
summary: The scent that constantly emits from its fur is so powerful that this Pokémon's companions will eventually lose their sense of smell.

name: Swirlix
summary: The sweet smell of cotton candy perfumes Swirlix's fluffy fur. This Pokémon spits out sticky string to tangle up its enemies.

name: Slurpuff
summary: By taking in a person's scent, it can sniff out their mental and physical condition. It's hoped that this skill will have many medical applications.

name: Inkay
summary: It spins while making its luminescent spots flash. These spots allow it to communicate with others by using different patterns of light.

name: Malamar
summary: Gazing at its luminescent spots will quickly induce a hypnotic state, putting the observer under Malamar's control.

name: Binacle
summary: After two Binacle find a suitably sized rock, they adhere themselves to it and live together. They cooperate to gather food during high tide.

name: Barbaracle
summary: Having an eye on each palm allows it to keep watch in all directions. In a pinch, its limbs start to act on their own to ensure the enemy's defeat.

name: Skrelp
summary: It drifts in the ocean, blending in with floating seaweed. When other Pokémon come to feast on the seaweed, Skrelp feasts on them instead.

name: Dragalge
summary: Dragalge generates dragon energy by sticking the plume on its head out above the ocean's surface and bathing it in sunlight.

name: Clauncher
summary: By detonating gas that accumulates in its right claw, this Pokémon launches water like a bullet. This is how Clauncher defeats its enemies.

name: Clawitzer
summary: Clawitzer's right arm is a cannon that launches projectiles made of seawater. Shots from a Clawitzer's cannon arm can sink a tanker.

name: Helioptile
summary: Secreting a thick inky substance from their scales since birth, helioptile leave trails of it wherever they go.

name: Heliolisk
summary: They use their ink to paint crude symbols on their paper like frills, expanding them to communicate to others.

name: Tyrunt
summary: This is an ancient Pokémon. It has a violent disposition, and it uses its hefty jaws to tear everything apart.

name: Tyrantrum
summary: After being buried for 100,000,000 years in a volcano, this Pokémon has been altered by the heat. It has the presence of a king, vicious but magnificent.

name: Amaura
summary: This Pokémon was successfully restored from a fossil. In the past, it lived with others of its kind in cold lands where there were fewer predators.

name: Aurorus
summary: Aurorus was restored from a fossil. It's said that when this Pokémon howls, auroras appear in the night sky.

name: Sylveon
summary: There's a Galarian fairy tale that describes a beautiful Sylveon vanquishing a dreadful dragon Pokémon.

name: Hawlucha
summary: It always strikes a pose before going for its finishing move. Sometimes opponents take advantage of that time to counterattack.

name: Dedenne
summary: Since Dedenne can't generate much electricity on its own, it steals electricity from outlets or other electric Pokémon.

name: Carbink
summary: The bands of iron spinning around it's core protect it from almost every kind of attack

name: Goomy
summary: Their horns are powerful sensors. As soon as Goomy pick up any sign of enemies, they go into hiding. This is how they've survived.

name: Sliggoo
summary: Although this Pokémon isn't very strong, its body is coated in a caustic slime that can melt through anything, so predators steer clear of it.

name: Goodra
summary: Sometimes it misunderstands instructions and appears dazed or bewildered. Many Trainers don't mind, finding this behavior to be adorable.

name: Klefki
summary: Radiating with electricity, it was commonly used to access electronically locked facilities.

name: Phantump
summary: After a lost child perished in the forest, their spirit possessed a tree stump, causing the spirit's rebirth as this Pokémon.

name: Trevenant
summary: A collection of lost spirits, with the sole purpose of defending wildlife from those who seek to destroy it.

name: Pumpkaboo
summary: When taking spirits to the afterlife, small Pumpkaboo prefer the spirits of children to those of adults.

name: Gourgeist
summary: Soft cries emanate from its body in the dead of night. The sounds are said to be the wails of spirits who are resting in the afterlife.

name: Bergmite
summary: They chill the air around them to -150 degrees Fahrenheit, freezing the water in the air into ice that they use as armor.

name: Avalugg
summary: As Avalugg moves about during the day, the cracks in its body deepen. The Pokémon's body returns to a pristine state overnight.

name: Noibat
summary: It is blind, and it spreads bright scales while fluttering about that keep predators from attacking it.

name: Noivern
summary: While it may look intimidating, it has a gentle and caring disposition. That said, it will shoot down anyone threatening its protégé with beams of light.

name: Xerneas
summary: When the horns on its head shine in seven colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.

name: Yveltal
summary: When its life comes to an end, it absorbs the life energy of every living thing and turns into a cocoon once more.

name: Zygarde
summary: Some say it can change to an even more powerful form when battling those who threaten the ecosystem.

name: Diancie
summary: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.

name: Hoopa
summary: It gathers things it likes and passes them through its loop to teleport them to a secret place.

name: Volcanion
summary: It expels its internal steam from the arms on its back. It has enough power to blow away a mountain.

name: Rowlet
summary: It sends its feathers, which are as sharp as blades, flying in attack. Its legs are strong, so its kicks are also formidable.

name: Dartrix
summary: This narcissistic Pokémon is a clean freak. If you don't groom it diligently, it will stop listening to you.

name: Decidueye
summary: It nocks its arrow quills and shoots them at opponents. When it simply can't afford to miss, it tugs the vine on its head to improve its focus.

name: Litten
summary: If you try too hard to get close to it, it won't open up to you. Even if you do grow close, giving it too much affection is still a no-no.

name: Torracat
summary: It can act spoiled if it grows close to its Trainer. A powerful Pokémon, its sharp claws can leave its Trainer's whole body covered in scratches.

name: Incineroar
summary: Although it's rough mannered and egotistical, it finds beating down unworthy opponents boring. It gets motivated for stronger opponents.

name: Popplio
summary: The balloons it inflates with its nose grow larger and larger as it practices day by day.

name: Brionne
summary: It gets excited when it sees a dance it doesn't know. This hard worker practices diligently until it can learn that dance.

name: Primarina
summary: To Primarina, every battle is a stage. It takes down its prey with beautiful singing and dancing.

name: Pikipek
summary: It pecks at trees with its hard beak. You can get some idea of its mood or condition from the rhythm of its pecking.

name: Trumbeak
summary: It can bend the tip of its beak to produce over a hundred different cries at will.

name: Toucannon
summary: They smack beaks with others of their kind to communicate. The strength and number of hits tell each other how they feel.

name: Yungoos
summary: An abrasive Pokemon that will do anything to get its way. Many children try to keep one as a pet, much to their parents' dismay.

name: Gumshoos
summary: This Pokemon finds joy in hurting and taking from others. Despite this fact, it seems to be good with children.

name: Grubbin
summary: Its natural enemies, like Rookidee, may flee rather than risk getting caught in its large mandibles that can snap thick tree branches.

name: Charjabug
summary: While its durable shell protects it from attacks, Charjabug strikes at enemies with jolts of electricity discharged from the tips of its jaws.

name: Vikavolt
summary: It builds up electricity in its abdomen, focuses it through its jaws, and then fires the electricity off in concentrated beams.

name: Crabrawler
summary: Its hard pincers are well suited to both offense and defense. Fights between two Crabrawler are like boxing matches.

name: Crabominable
summary: It stores coldness in its pincers and pummels its foes. It can even smash thick walls of ice to bits!

name: Oricorio
summary: It wins the hearts of its enemies with its passionate dancing and then uses the opening it creates to burn them up with blazing flames.

name: Cutiefly
summary: It propels itself forward by combusting its sweat, which creates a small explosion similar to gunpowder.

name: Ribombee
summary: During the New Year night, multiple Ribombee can be seen fluttering in the sky, creating eye-striking explosions via their peculiar powder.

name: Rockruff
summary: This Pokémon intimidates opponents by striking the ground with the rocks on its neck. The moment an opponent flinches, Rockruff attacks.

name: Lycanroc
summary: With swift movements, this Pokémon gradually backs its prey into a corner. Lycanroc's fangs are always aimed toward opponents' weak spots.

name: Wishiwashi
summary: Individually, they're incredibly weak. It's by gathering up into schools that they're able to confront opponents.

name: Mareanie
summary: The first symptom of its sting is numbness. The next is an itching sensation so intense that it's impossible to resist the urge to claw at your skin.

name: Toxapex
summary: Within the poison sac in its body is a poison so toxic that Pokémon as large as Wailord will still be suffering three days after it first takes effect.

name: Mudbray
summary: It eats dirt to create mud and smears this mud all over its feet, giving them the grip needed to walk on rough terrain without slipping.

name: Mudsdale
summary: Mud that hardens around a Mudsdale's legs sets harder than stone. It's so hard that it allows this Pokémon to scrap a truck with a single kick.

name: Dewpider
summary: It forms a water bubble at the rear of its body and then covers its head with it. Meeting another Dewpider means comparing water-bubble sizes.

name: Araquanid
summary: It launches water bubbles with its legs, drowning prey within the bubbles. This Pokémon can then take its time to savor its meal.

name: Fomantis
summary: When bathed in sunlight, this Pokémon emits a pleasantly sweet scent, which causes bug Pokémon to gather around it.

name: Lurantis
summary: The petals on this Pokémon's arms are thin and super sharp, and they can fire laser beams if Lurantis gathers light first.

name: Morelull
summary: Morelull live in forests that stay dark even during the day. They scatter flickering spores that put enemies to sleep.

name: Shiinotic
summary: Its flickering spores lure in prey and put them to sleep. Once this Pokémon has its prey snoozing, it drains their vitality with its fingertips.

name: Salandit
summary: Its venom sacs produce a fluid that this Pokémon then heats up with the flame in its tail. This process creates Salandit's poisonous gas.

name: Salazzle
summary: The winner of competitions between Salazzle is decided by which one has the most male Salandit with it.

name: Stufful
summary: The way it protects itself by flailing its arms may be an adorable sight, but stay well away. This is flailing that can snap thick tree trunks.

name: Bewear
summary: Once it accepts you as a friend, it tries to show its affection with a hug. Letting it do that is dangerous. It could easily shatter your bones.

name: Bounsweet
summary: When under attack, it secretes a sweet and delicious sweat. The scent only calls more enemies to it.

name: Steenee
summary: Any Corvisquire that pecks at this Pokémon will be greeted with a smack from its sepals followed by a sharp kick.

name: Tsareena
summary: A kick from the hardened tips of this Pokémon's legs leaves a wound in the opponent's body and soul that will never heal.

name: Comfey
summary: Comfey picks flowers with its vine and decorates itself with them. For some reason, flowers won't wither once they're attached to a Comfey.

name: Oranguru
summary: It knows the forest inside and out. If it comes across a wounded Pokémon, Oranguru will gather medicinal herbs to treat it.

name: Passimian
summary: Passimian live in groups of about 20, with each member performing an assigned role. Through cooperation, the group survives.

name: Wimpod
summary: It's nature's cleaner. It eats anything and everything, including garbage and rotten things. The ground near its nest is always clean.

name: Golisopod
summary: It will do anything to win, taking advantage of every opening and finishing opponents off with the small claws on its front legs.

name: Sandygast
summary: Sandygast mainly inhabits beaches. It takes control of anyone who puts their hand into its mouth, forcing them to make its body bigger.

name: Palossand
summary: Palossand is known as the Beach Nightmare. It pulls its prey down into the sand by controlling the sand itself, and then it sucks out their souls.

name: Pyukumuku
summary: It lives in warm, shallow waters. If it encounters a foe, it will spit out its internal organs as a means to punch them.

name: Type: Null
summary: Rumor has it that the theft of top-secret research notes led to a new instance of this Pokémon being created in the Galar region.

name: Silvally
summary: A solid bond of trust between this Pokémon and its Trainer awakened the strength hidden within Silvally. It can change its type at will.

name: Minior
summary: It lives in the ozone layer, where it becomes food for stronger Pokémon. When it tries to run away, it falls to the ground.

name: Komala
summary: It stays asleep from the moment it's born. When it falls into a deep sleep, it stops moving altogether.

name: Turtonator
summary: Eating sulfur in its volcanic habitat is what causes explosive compounds to develop in its shell. Its droppings are also dangerously explosive.

name: Togedemaru
summary: With the long hairs on its back, this Pokémon takes in electricity from other electric Pokémon. It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.

name: Mimikyu
summary: Said to be a furious spirit that inhabited a popular doll. When said doll is damaged, the hatred of the specter takes form.

name: Bruxish
summary: It burrows beneath the sand, radiating psychic power from the protuberance on its head. It waits for prey as it surveys the area.

name: Drampa
summary: The mountains it calls home are nearly two miles in height. On rare occasions, it descends to play with the children living in the towns below.

name: Dhelmise
summary: After a piece of seaweed merged with debris from a sunken ship, it was reborn as this ghost Pokémon.

name: Jangmo-o
summary: Jangmo-o strikes its scales to communicate with others of its kind. Its scales are actually fur that's become as hard as metal.

name: Hakamo-o
summary: Before attacking its enemies, it clashes its scales together and roars. Its sharp claws shred the opposition.

name: Kommo-o
summary: It clatters its tail scales to unnerve opponents. This Pokémon will battle only those who stand steadfast in the face of this display.

name: Tapu Koko
summary: Although it's called a guardian deity, if a person or Pokémon puts it in a bad mood, it will become a malevolent deity and attack.

name: Tapu Lele
summary: It heals the wounds of people and Pokémon by sprinkling them with its sparkling scales. This guardian deity is worshiped on Akala.

name: Tapu Bulu
summary: Although it's called a guardian deity, it's violent enough to crush anyone it sees as an enemy.

name: Tapu Fini
summary: This guardian deity of Poni Island manipulates water. Because it lives deep within a thick fog, it came to be both feared and revered.

name: Cosmog
summary: Even though its helpless, gaseous body can be blown away by the slightest breeze, it doesn't seem to care.

name: Cosmoem
summary: The king who ruled Alola in times of antiquity called it the "cocoon of the stars" and built an altar to worship it.

name: Solgaleo
summary: Sometimes the result of its opening an Ultra Wormhole is that energy and life-forms from other worlds are called here to this world.

name: Lunala
summary: Records of it exist in writings from long, long ago, where it was known by the name "the beast that calls the moon."

name: Nihilego
summary: A life-form from another world, it was dubbed a UB and is thought to produce a strong neurotoxin.

name: Buzzwole
summary: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

name: Pheromosa
summary: A life-form that lives in another world, its body is thin and supple, but it also possesses great power.

name: Xurkitree
summary: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

name: Celesteela
summary: One of the dangerous UBs, high energy readings can be detected coming from both of its huge arms.

name: Kartana
summary: This Ultra Beast's body, which is as thin as paper, is like a sharpened sword.

name: Guzzlord
summary: Although it's alien to this world and a danger here, it's apparently a common organism in the world where it normally lives.

name: Necrozma
summary: It looks somehow pained as it rages around in search of light, which serves as its energy. It's apparently from another world.

name: Magearna
summary: It synchronizes its consciousness with others to understand their feelings. This faculty makes it useful for taking care of people.

name: Marshadow
summary: It slips into the shadows of others and mimics their powers and movements. As it improves, it becomes stronger than those it's imitating.

name: Poipole
summary: This Ultra Beast is well enough liked to be chosen as a first partner in its own world.

name: Naganadel
summary: It stores hundreds of liters of poisonous liquid inside its body. It is one of the organisms known as UBs.

name: Stakataka
summary: It appeared from an Ultra Wormhole. Each one appears to be made up of many life-forms stacked one on top of each other.

name: Blacephalon
summary: It slithers toward people. Then, without warning, it triggers the explosion of its own head. It's apparently one kind of Ultra Beast.

name: Zeraora
summary: It electrifies its claws and tears its opponents apart with them. Even if they dodge its attack, they'll be electrocuted by the flying sparks.

name: Meltan
summary: It melts particles of iron and other metals found in the subsoil, so it can absorb them into its body of molten steel.

name: Melmetal
summary: Revered long ago for its capacity to create iron from nothing, for some reason it has come back to life after 3,000 years.

name: Grookey
summary: It attacks with rapid jolts of its stick. As it strikes with amazing speed, it gets more and more charged.

name: Thwackey
summary: When it's drumming out rapid beats in battle, it gets so caught up in the rhythm that it won't even notice that it's already knocked out its opponent.

name: Rillaboom
summary: Its ferocious drumming summons violent thunderstorms. It uses wind currents to direct its electric attacks.

name: Scorbunny
summary: It has special pads on the backs of its feet, and one on its nose. Once it's raring to fight, these pads radiate tremendous heat.

name: Raboot
summary: It kicks berries right off the branches of trees and then juggles them with its feet, practicing its footwork.

name: Cinderace
summary: It's skilled at both offense and defense, and it gets pumped up when cheered on. But if it starts showboating, it could put itself in a tough spot.

name: Sobble
summary: When it gets wet, its skin changes color, and this Pokemon becomes invisible as if it were camouflaged.

name: Drizzile
summary: Highly intelligent but also very lazy, it keeps enemies out of its territory by laying traps everywhere.

name: Inteleon
summary: Its nictitating membranes let it pick out foes' weak points so it can precisely blast them with water that shoots from its fingertips at Mach 3.

name: Skwovet
summary: It eats berries nonstop, a habit that has made it more resilient than it looks. It'll show up on farms, searching for yet more berries.

name: Greedent
summary: Common throughout the Galar region, this Pokémon has strong teeth and can chew through the toughest of berry shells.

name: Rookidee
summary: Jumping nimbly about, this small-bodied Pokémon takes advantage of even the slightest opportunity to disorient larger opponents.

name: Corvisquire
summary: The lessons of many harsh battles have taught it how to accurately judge an opponent's strength.

name: Corviknight
summary: With their great intellect and flying skills, these Pokémon very successfully act as the Galar region's airborne taxi service.

name: Blipbug
summary: Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.

name: Dottler
summary: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.

name: Orbeetle
summary: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what's around it, and what's around it can include things over six miles away.

name: Nickit
summary: They will create clouds under their paws and use them to float, blending in with the sky. They will often float up to mountains and steal eggs from bird Pokemon's nests.

name: Thievul
summary: Creating clouds under its paws, it races through the skies- swooping down below if it spots something shiny.

name: Gossifleur
summary: It whirls around in the wind while singing a joyous song. This delightful display has charmed many into raising this Pokémon.

name: Eldegoss
summary: The cotton on the head of this Pokémon can be spun into a glossy, gorgeous yarn, a Galar regional specialty.

name: Wooloo
summary: If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won't be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.

name: Dubwool
summary: Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.

name: Chewtle
summary: It starts off battles by attacking with its rock-hard horn, but as soon as the opponent flinches, this Pokémon bites down and never lets go.

name: Drednaw
summary: This Pokémon rapidly extends its retractable neck to sink its sharp fangs into distant enemies and take them down.

name: Yamper
summary: This gluttonous Pokémon only assists people with their work because it wants treats. As it runs, it crackles with electricity.

name: Boltund
summary: It sends electricity through its legs to boost their strength. Running at top speed, it easily breaks 50 mph.

name: Rolycoly
summary: It can race around like a unicycle, even on rough, rocky terrain. Burning coal sustains it.

name: Carkol
summary: By rapidly rolling its legs, it can travel at over 18 mph. The temperature of the flames it breathes exceeds 1,800 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Coalossal
summary: While it's engaged in battle, its mountain of coal will burn bright red, sending off sparks that scorch the surrounding area.

name: Applin
summary: As soon as it's born, it burrows into an apple. Not only does the apple serve as its food source, but the flavor of the fruit determines its evolution.

name: Flapple
summary: It flies on wings of apple skin and spits a powerful acid. It can also change its shape into that of an apple.

name: Appletun
summary: Its body is covered in sweet nectar, and the skin on its back is especially yummy. Children used to have it as a snack.

name: Silicobra
summary: It spews sand from its nostrils. While the enemy is blinded, it burrows into the ground to hide.

name: Sandaconda
summary: Its unique style of coiling allows it to blast sand out of its sand sac more efficiently.

name: Cramorant
summary: This hungry Pokémon swallows Arrokuda whole. Occasionally, it makes a mistake and tries to swallow a Pokémon other than its preferred prey.

name: Arrokuda
summary: After it's eaten its fill, its movements become extremely sluggish. That's when Cramorant swallows it up.

name: Barraskewda
summary: It spins its tail fins to propel itself, surging forward at speeds of over 100 knots before ramming prey and spearing into them.

name: Toxel
summary: It manipulates the chemical makeup of its poison to produce electricity. The voltage is weak, but it can cause a tingling paralysis.

name: Toxtricity
summary: This short-tempered and aggressive Pokémon chugs stagnant water to absorb any toxins it might contain.

name: Sizzlipede
summary: Its tiny metal shell floats around its central core. Its inexperience with its gravity powers keeps it erratically afloat.

name: Centiskorch
summary: Its segmented metal body provides incredible protection and flexibility giving it. Centiskorch has a unique power to manipulate gravity, allowing it to alter its weight and create localized gravitational fields.

name: Clobbopus
summary: Its tentacles tear off easily, but it isn't alarmed when that happens, it knows they'll grow back. It's about as smart as a three-year-old.

name: Grapploct
summary: Searching for an opponent to test its skills against, it emerges onto land. Once the battle is over, it returns to the sea.

name: Sinistea
summary: The teacup in which this Pokémon makes its home is a famous piece of antique tableware. Many forgeries are in circulation.

name: Polteageist
summary: Leaving leftover black tea unattended is asking for this Pokémon to come along and pour itself into it, turning the tea into a new Polteageist.

name: Hatenna
summary: Aware of its cuteness, it invites itself in the dens of other Pokemon and slowly fills them with spider webs.

name: Hattrem
summary: Its leg-hairs have enough power to bend a metal pole in two. Because of this, they have no natural predators, and thrive in gloomy forests.

name: Hatterene
summary: It plays with its prey with unimaginable cruelty. Usually, it leaves the poor victim's life hanging on by a thread, literally.

name: Impidimp
summary: It sneaks into people's homes, stealing things and feasting on the negative energy of the frustrated occupants.

name: Morgrem
summary: With sly cunning, it tries to lure people into the woods. Some believe it to have the power to make crops grow.

name: Grimmsnarl
summary: Its hairs work like muscle fibers. When its hairs unfurl, they latch on to opponents, ensnaring them as tentacles would.

name: Twirlaroon
